      "chunk_length": 81,
      "enhanced_tags": [],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.978901"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "It's curious that we both made resolutions to lose weight, isn't it? I mean, most people overeat a bit at Christmas, then diet in January.",
      "chunk_id": "a0f6694e-2cee-450c-b14e-04ba23e56782",
      "chunk_index": 1,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 138,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "BI",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.981129"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "In this programme, we'll be asking where the attitudes behind fat shaming come from.We'll be hearing how anti-fat attitudes are often implicit or unconscious.",
      "chunk_id": "7cdcb1f3-f5c1-44c0-ae42-bc9f0c8a02fe",
      "chunk_index": 2,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 158,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "CI",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.983361"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "OK, we'll find out the answer later.",
      "chunk_id": "21cee3a5-fcac-4ec5-b21f-5692d8a1af6e",
      "chunk_index": 3,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 36,
      "enhanced_tags": [],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.985459"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Professor Sagai says the term abyss was coined in the mid-1980s.",
      "chunk_id": "b2fafb08-815c-44de-9ee3-1db5e7defd7f",
      "chunk_index": 4,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 64,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "ES",
        "AI"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.987557"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "It originally meant an individual medical problem, something to be discussed between patient and doctor, but over time, abyss has become a term of discrimination and abuse.Psychology professor Chris Crandall has been involved in Harvard University's implicit bias projects, most famous for revealing racial prejudice.The tests also measure other kinds of biases, including weight.",
      "chunk_id": "f78bef87-d3ab-471f-a6ef-55b1057f114c",
      "chunk_index": 5,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 380,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "RSI",
        "CI",
        "VaR",
        "BI",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.990107"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "The beliefs we hold about other people are hidden from conscious awareness.So what goes through our mind, consciously or unconsciously, when we see very fat people?Here's Professor Crandall speaking to BBC World Service's The Why Factor.",
      "chunk_id": "cc36f6c5-a202-450a-8229-fb18e27cb776",
      "chunk_index": 6,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 237,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "CI",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.992496"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "There is a commonly held prejudice that fat people are responsible for their condition because they're lazy, greedy or lacking in moral fibre.The ability or determination to behave ethically or with self-control",
      "chunk_id": "021fbc01-bf3f-49bd-859d-d77d5b062531",
      "chunk_index": 7,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 211,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "BI",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.994801"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "This leads some to treat them with scorn, a strong feeling of contempt or disrespect.In reality, of course, weight isn't just about individual choices.How fat you are is also determined by environment and genetics.",
      "chunk_id": "269af349-bc08-45a6-9ff0-09def4a4cdab",
      "chunk_index": 8,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 214,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.997113"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "So if it doesn't cause problems, maybe you can have that second slice of cake after all, Georgina.Thanks, Neil, but I don't want to spoil my appetite for the quiz question you asked.",
      "chunk_id": "65e91fb2-488e-4b48-aea5-7cd59b28be27",
      "chunk_index": 9,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 182,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "UI",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.999375"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Fat is an issue affecting millions of adults in the UK alone, and with studies suggesting that obesity might be a negative factor linked to Covid-19, it's one that could affect millions more.",
      "chunk_id": "1d89d3e6-4332-4399-a557-7ff1c8cf1355",
      "chunk_index": 10,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d1176706",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_What is fat-shaming_.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 191,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:10.001648"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Fat shaming is criticizing and humiliating someone for being fat, or showing them scorn, feelings of contempt or disrespect.Or it could also involve believing they lack moral fibre, the ability to behave correctly or with self-control.That's all for this programme, but to find out more about your own implicit biases based on race, sexuality or weight, search online for",
      "chunk_id": "2261e5ba-b463-450c-a7d7-321c7053e8ea",
